-- mid.mdk RE-EXPORTS base's `double` via `export import` (a `DUse True`).  It has
-- NO `DFunDef` for `double` of its own — it only forwards base's.  Pre-fix, the
-- mangle pass computed mid's export set from LOCALLY-defined names only, so
-- `double` never entered mid's exports; entry's reference to it got NO rename entry
-- and stayed a bare, orphaned `double` with no backing define → emit-time
-- "unbound variable 'double'".  The fix follows the `DUse True` chain so mid's
-- export of `double` carries base as the definer, and entry's reference mangles to
-- `<base>__double`.
export import base.{double}
